{% block introduction %}
	The LFDS Vocabulary provides a minimal set of classes on which the LFDS and IOPA application profiles are build.
  These are intended to support the Legislative Financial and Digital Statements within EU institutions and the Interoperability Assessments mandated by the Interoperable Europe Act.
</p>
{% endblock %}


{% block summary %}
<section id="abstract">
    <h2>Abstract</h2>
The LFDS Vocabulary is a simplified, reusable and extensible data model that provides a minimum set of classes and properties for
describing Interoperability Assessments.
</section>
